[attribute=value] {
  ...
}

In this example, the [attribute=value] CSS selector selects any elements that have the style attribute and whose value is equal to rgb(128, 128, 128). The curly braces {} group all of the selectors inside of the [] square brackets, so they will be applied together.<|endoftext|>

You can use the following CSS Selector to target an Element that contains the specified Style Attibute:
```css
[style*='background-color: rgb(128, 128, 128)'] {
    /* Your styles go here */
}
```
This Selector will select any Elements with a Style Attibute whose Value contains the specified String. In this case, it is looking for an Element with a Style Attibute whose Value is equal to 'background-color: rgb(128, 128, 128); '. If there are multiple matches, they will be combined into one Set and processed by the Selector.<|endoftext|>

