% Display the equation and its roots
\begin{document}
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|c|c|} \hline 
Polynomial & Solutions \\ \hline 
$P(x) = 0$ & None\\ \hline
$P'(x) = 6x^2 + 8x - 10$ & One root at $\pm \frac{-b}{6}$\\ \hline
$P''(x) = 12x + 4$ & Infinitely many roots (algebraic branchpoints) at $\pm b$ and their complex conjugates\\ \hline
\end{tabular}
\caption{Fundamental Theorem of Algberth} \label{fta}
\end{center}
\end{document}

In this document, we use the command \usepackage[options]{geometry} to specify the desired page geometry. The total option specifies the overall dimensions of the document, including the width and height of the pages. In this case, we have specified 170mm for the left-hand side and 257mm for the right-hand side.

